text.section:
Of the 10 Council members:
1 shall be a member of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of the Senate;
1 shall be a member of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
1 shall be the Attorney General or the Attorney General's designee;
1 shall be a nongovernmental attorney who practices before the Office of Administrative Hearings;
2 shall be secretaries or designees from departments involved in the adjudication of contested cases;
2 shall represent the Maryland State Bar Association; and
2 shall be from the general public.
